  <title component="profesor"><nbsp/>([@@@@@@@@@] mins)</title>

  <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Display:</p>
<p style="text-align:center"><m>6\times5={?}</m> <m>6\times{?}=30</m> <m>{?}\times5=30</m></p>
<p><q>Hoy encontramos el número desconocido en ecuaciones de multiplicación</q></p>
<p><q>¿En qué fue diferente encontrar un factor desconocido de encontrar un producto desconocido?</q> (If we didn’t know the product, we could skip-count by the number the right number of times, like 5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30. If we didn’t know one of the factors, we might have to skip-count by the number enough times to get to the product. If we didn’t know one of the factors, we might not know what to skip-count by, just the number of counts.)</p>

</subsubsection>



